column5: Here are some pics from the event earlier today  We ended catching 35 perch in total, and had a great time meeting everyone. All in all a very good day on the lake!                    Thanks,  Ryan
Well it nice to see you guys made out alright.It was also nice talking with you and cant wait to give those baits a try. Dan

Nice report Ryan, and thanks again for the lures, it was very generous.  I'll let you know how they perform for me.  Its funny, the girl in your pictures has her cuffs on her pants turned up and when she was walking across the ice in the distance, before we knew who you were, we thought her boots were the florescent orange colour.  Gave us a chuckle.  Joey
Thats my girlfriend Ann, I curled them up so its easy to find her when she tries to run away from me!
Nice to meet you in person Ryan !  Wayne
thanks for sharing. Sure does look cold there.
Nice meeting you as well Wayne, I had hoped to talk to you a little at the end of the day but you were already gone.
Thanks again for the small jigs Ryan...Big Cliff and I will give them a workout today up at Uncle Jack's Pond for crappie...
No problem, Devon was catching perch on this greenish yellow one without any minnows. I tried  that with a white one and pink one, no luck.
